2. **`Set A ∼ 𝒫 A`**: By definition, `Set A` is exactly `𝒫 A`, so this is trivially true (but Lean needs an explicit proof).
3. **`Set B ∼ 𝒫 B`**: Similarly, this is trivially true.
4. **`𝒫 A ∼ 𝒫 B`**: Chain all the above using transitivity of equinumerosity.

